# 1. Sort the array → x

# 2. Calculate:
#    r = (p / 100) * (n - 1)     r = 0.75 * 3  ->  (2.25)  ->  75 th according 

# 3. Split r into:
#    i = int(floor(r))     # integer part   ->   2
#    f = r - i             # fractional part      ->   0.25

# 4. Apply formula:
#    P = x[i] + f * (x[i + 1] - x[i])   ->     12 + 0.25 * (33 - 12)    ->  12 + 0.25(21)   ->  12 + 5.25

print(np.percentile(arr,75))            



